  "prompt": "What are some islands located in the Pacific Ocean?",
  "response": "The Pacific Ocean, the largest ocean on Earth, is home to numerous islands, ranging from tiny atolls to large landmasses. Here are some notable islands and island groups in the Pacific Ocean:\n\n### **Polynesia**\n1. **Hawaiian Islands** (USA)\n   - Hawaii (Big Island)\n   Maui\n   Oahu\n   Kauai\n   Molokai\n2. **Samoa**\n   - Upolu\n   Savai'i\n3. **Tonga**\n   - Tongatapu\n   Vava'u\n4. **French Polynesia**\n   - Tahiti\n   Bora Bora\n   Moorea\n5. **Cook Islands**\n   - Rarotonga\n   Aitutaki\n\n### **Melanesia**\n1. **Fiji**\n   - Viti Levu\n   Vanua Levu\n2. **Vanuatu**\n   - Espiritu Santo\n   Efate\n3. **Solomon Islands**\n   - Guadalcanal\n   Malaita\n4. **New Caledonia** (France)\n   - Grande Terre\n\n### **Micronesia**\n1. **Guam** (USA)\n2. **Northern Mariana Islands** (USA)\n   - Saipan\n   Tinian\n3. **Federated States of Micronesia**\n   - Pohnpei\n   Chuuk\n4. **Palau**\n   - Koror\n   Babeldaob\n5. **Marshall Islands**\n   - Majuro\n   Kwajalein\n\n### **Other Notable Islands**\n1. **Easter Island** (Chile)\n2. **Gal\u00e1pagos Islands** (Ecuador)\n3. **Philippines**\n   - Luzon\n   Mindanao\n   Palawan\n4. **Indonesia**\n   - Papua (shared with Papua New Guinea)\n   Sulawesi\n   Sumatra\n5. **Japan**\n   - Honshu\n   Hokkaido\n   Kyushu\n   Shikoku\n6. **New Zealand**\n   - North Island\n   South Island\n\nThis list highlights just a fraction of the thousands of islands scattered across the Pacific Ocean, each with its own unique culture, geography, and history.",
